openconnector
Class AbstractConnector

java.lang.Object
  openconnector.AbstractConnector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Connector
public abstract class AbstractConnector
extends java.lang.Object
implements Connector

An abstract implementation of the Connector interfaces that all connectors should extend. This provides basic configuration support and throws UnsupportedOperationExceptions for most methods.

Extending this class is not required to use the connector with IdentityIQ, but it is required if you want to test and maintain the connector using XModule.

doSystemItems

protected Result doSystemItems(Request req,
                               java.util.List<Item> items,
                               java.lang.String id)
Helper for provision, process the list of system items. Result handling is awkward because a Request can only have one Result, but here the Request is being split into several actions each having a potentially different Result.

The typical cases are handled adequately with these rules:

  • if there were any non-system items with this request, then the result from the previous create or update call will not change status but might add messages

  • if there were no non-system items with this request, then the first system item processed defines the Result status for the request

While it seems funny to not try to merge Results of multiple system items, in practice this doesn't happen.

buildOptions

public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> buildOptions(Request request)
Build up the options that will be passed down to each of the operations that have options. (enable, disable, unlock, changePassword.

In any given request there can arguments at the request level and/or item level. These arguments will be flattened into a single Map and given to each method in the options method parameter.

In some cases operation might require additional values sent over in the request in the form of other Items.

If there are additional items present in the Request they will also be merged into the options map by name of the item as the key and the value of the item as the value of the key in the options map.

The arguments from the request, the item, and then finally any additional included items are added.

There should not be any key conflict, but if they do occur the arguments and the item names the item will be skipped and an error will be sent to the log.

Parameters:
request -
Returns:
a Map of the request and item args and and any additional items name and values.

setPassword

public Result setPassword(java.lang.String id,
                          java.lang.String newPassword,
                          java.lang.String currentPassword,
                          java.util.Date expiration,
                          java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> options)
                   throws ConnectorException,
                          ObjectNotFoundException,
                          java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
Set the password for the given object to the newPassword. The current password may be passed in, but is not typically required. If available, the current password should be passed in, since some resources require this for full behavior around password policy checking, password history, etc...

If there are additional Items present as part of the Request they will be merged into the options map by name of the item. The value stored for each name (key) is the value found on the Item.

Parameters:
id - The value for the identity attribute.
newPassword - The password to set for the account.
currentPassword - The current password of the account. This should be provided if available, but is not always required.
expiration - The expiration date for the password.
options - An optional map of options that can provide additional information about the password change.
Throws:
ConnectorException - If the operation fails.
ObjectNotFoundException - If the object to set the password on cannot be found.
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - If the SET_PASSWORD feature is not supported.
